                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <hr>

            <h2 class="fw-semibold">Querying Health Topics</h2>
            <p>The health topics API supports searching by keyword and filtering by category or type. A simple search looks like this:</p>

            <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>curl -H "X-Api-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \
  "https://api.meducateapi.com/api/topics/search?query=diabetes"</code></pre>

            <p>To retrieve a specific topic by name:</p>

            <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>curl -H "X-Api-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \
  "https://api.meducateapi.com/api/topics/diabetes"</code></pre>

            <p>See the <a href="/docs">full API documentation</a> for all available endpoints, query parameters, and response schemas.</p>

            <hr>

            <h2 class="fw-semibold">Data Sources</h2>
            <p>Health topic data is sourced from:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>MedlinePlus</strong> — U.S. National Library of Medicine, covering 2,000+ health topics updated daily. The primary source for topic inclusion: if a topic is on MedlinePlus, it's in Meducate. If it's removed from MedlinePlus, it's retired from Meducate automatically.</li>
                <li><strong>PubMed</strong> — peer-reviewed biomedical literature from the NLM. Used to enrich topics with additional research context.</li>
            </ul>

